# Storefront App

## Purpose

The `storefront` app is the customer-facing commerce experience for storefront browsing and checkout.
It is distinct from the marketing site in `apps/web`.

## Structure

```text
apps/storefront/src/
├── app/
│   ├── [lang]/
│   │   ├── layout.tsx
│   │   ├── page.tsx
│   │   ├── products/[id]/page.tsx
│   │   └── checkout/
│   └── api/storefront/[[...rest]]/route.ts
├── components/
│   ├── app/
│   ├── layout/
│   └── shared/
├── hooks/
├── lib/
├── stores/
├── env.ts
└── proxy.ts
```

## Data and API

- Use `@dukkani/orpc` utilities via local `lib/orpc.ts`.
- Keep request and response typing aligned with shared schemas from `@dukkani/common`.
- Route API calls through `app/api/storefront/[[...rest]]/route.ts` when app-local API entry is needed.

## State Management

- Keep cart and filter state in zustand stores under `stores/`.
- Derive computed cart values in selectors or utility functions, not duplicated in UI components.

## i18n and Routing

- Keep user-visible routes under `app/[lang]/...`.
- Use locale helpers from `lib/i18n.ts` and keep locale-aware links consistent.

## Error Handling

- Reuse shared error patterns and helper functions (`lib/error.ts`).
- Do not inline generic error toasts; keep error mapping centralized.

## Best Practices

- Use server components by default and opt into `"use client"` only when needed.
- Keep checkout, cart, and product-card logic modular in `components/app/`.
- Reuse UI primitives from `@dukkani/ui`.
- Keep storefront-specific logic in this app and shared cross-app logic in packages.
